```go
func recover() any
```
Allows a program to manage behavior of a panicking goroutine. Must be called inside a **deferred** function. During normal execution, recover returns nil. If the current goroutine is panicking, recover captures the value given to panic and resumes normal execution.

```go
defer func() {
    if r := recover(); r != nil {
        log.Println("Recovered:", r)
    }
}()
```

