```go
type Seq[V any] func(yield func(V) bool)
```
Push-style iterator (Go 1.23+). Used with range:
```go
func All[V any](s []V) iter.Seq[V] {
    return func(yield func(V) bool) {
        for _, v := range s {
            if !yield(v) { return }
        }
    }
}
for v := range All(mySlice) { ... }
```

```go
func iter.Pull[V any](seq Seq[V]) (next func() (V, bool), stop func())
```
Converts a push iterator to pull style. Must call stop() when done.
```go
next, stop := iter.Pull(seq)
defer stop()
for {
    v, ok := next()
    if !ok { break }
    fmt.Println(v)
}
```

